column5: Heading to Guelph for the 2nd game between Battalion and Storm. Nothing fancy. Just good food.
Stampede ranch on Woodlawn east of the Hanlon expwy

Angels diner on Wellington St at Gordon, or Vienna restaurant on MacDonnell street in the downtown.  If I had to choose one or the other, it would be the Vienna.  Also close to the game.  I probably wouldn't go with Stampede myself, but your mileage may vary!
Thanks for the tips.  On a side note. What is the going rate for parking?
Free parking. Corner of fountain st. E and Neeve st. Western hotel burgers and steaks. Right downtown beside arena. Park and walk to food and game.
The Woolwich Arms aka The Wooly... Great beers and eats.
I wouldn't waste my time coming to Guelph. North bay is going to lose and you'll be able to see the cup up there after game #4.  :-)
I've also got tickets to the Memorial Cup. Besides, I'm a Colts fan first.
Most places were full at 5pm. Ended up eating at a Thai place connected to the arena. Good food.  From a layout standpoint, that arena is the best of the new buildings in the O that I've been to.
